cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the capacity of K-user Gaussian Symmetric Interference Channel, which is a fundamental problem in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a novel precoding technique for wireless networks to improve the achievable sum-rate, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper deals with interference alignment and precoding techniques, which are important signal processing techniques used in wireless communication systems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the achievable sum-rate in wireless networks, which is relevant to multimedia applications that require high data rates. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper proposes a computational technique (Compute-and-Forward transform) to approximate the capacity of the interference channel, which falls under the domain of computational engineering.
